\begin_layout Standard
We can obtain an expression for the juvenile abundance,
 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{y,J}$
\end_inset

,
 needed for 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:self-staged"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 using a geometric progression.
 Notation is as in Section
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "sec:Methods"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 and assume that survival continues "forever" so that we can use infinite sums (and so we can avoid several other inconveniences in the CKMR equations that would require an explicit representation of age structure).
 Writing 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{a}=\Phi\left(1,a\right)$
\end_inset

 for one-year survival at age 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

,
 we begin by looking at how the adult population changes from year-to-year.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If we did have an age-structured model,
 then to find the abundance in year 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $y+1$
\end_inset

 of those individuals who age from 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $a+1$
\end_inset

,
 we only need consider survival
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N\left(y+1,a+1\right)=\phi_{a}N\left(y,a\right),
\]

\end_inset

where here we use 
\begin_inset Formula $N(y,a)$
\end_inset

 to indicate the abundance of individuals of age 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 at year 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

.
 Then if we look at the abundance at age 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 from one year to the next,
 we need to consider population rate of increase,
 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N\left(y+1,a\right)=e^{r}N\left(y,a\right).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Combining these two equations and letting 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho=e^{r}$
\end_inset

,
 we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N\left(y,a+1\right)=\phi_{a}N\left(y-1,a\right)=\frac{\phi_{a}}{\rho}N\left(y,a\right),
\]

\end_inset

so,
 given the abundance of individuals of age 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 in year 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

,
 we can write the abundance of individuals age 
\begin_inset Formula $a+t$
\end_inset

 as
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N\left(y,a+t\right)=\left(\frac{\phi_{a}}{\rho}\right)^{t}N\left(y,a\right),
\]

\end_inset


